==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Lyrid
<hw>Ly"rid</hw> <pr>(l⟦imac⟧"r⟦icr⟧d)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Astron.)</fld> <def>One of the group of shooting stars which come
into the air in certain years on or about the 19th of April; -- so
called because the apparent path among the stars if traced backwards
crosses the constellation <etsep>Lyra</etsep>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Lyrie</ent>⟦br⟧
